An incorrect figure was removed. The figure showed glutamate overlaid with the structure of arylcyclohxylamines. Arylcyclohexylamines bind to a site distinct from glutamate and NMDA on the NMDA receptor. Thus this comparison is meaningless and misleading. Likewise the structural overlap is poor. Arylcyclohexylamines are noncompetitive (really uncompetitive i.e. use-dependent) inhibitors that bind to the PCP-binding site. The PCP binding site is inside the NMDA receptor channel far from the glutamate site. Arylcyclohexylamines are not known to bind to the glutamate site. However glutamate site antagonists (competitive antagonists) also induce dissociative effects.
